The '''Nicolae Iorga Institute of History''' ({{lang-ro|Institutul de Istorie „Nicolae Iorga”}}; abbreviation: '''IINI''') in [[Bucharest]] is an institution of research in the field of [[history]] under the auspices of the [[Romanian Academy]]. The institute was founded on 15 April 1937 by Romanian historian and its first director, [[Nicolae Iorga]],
